            "answer_text": "Thanks for the A2A! The same way boxers can take punches that would put the rest of us in the hospital. And how there are people who can eat 90 hot dogs in 20 minutes. Training. Lots of it. Endurance. Early in my music career when I was just a kid, I got a gig playing keyboards at a private club that was open 24/7. It was in an old converted Kmart store and had a half dozen stages scattered around. Non-stop live music. I was one of the acts. I would have to play 40 minute sets, with two hour breaks. I'd be there for 12-15 hours sometimes, napping & playing. It was the closest thing to musical torture I ever endured. It was a true blessing because the experience gave me Olympic endurance and taught me how to keep playing even when I couldn't even feel my hands anymore. ",
